  "explanation": "The defendant committed a serious breach of fiduciary duty by embezzling $25,000 from their employer. As an accountant, the defendant was placed in a position of trust, making this crime particularly damaging to the employer-employee relationship. However, several mitigating factors have been taken into consideration. The defendant has no prior criminal record, demonstrating that this is an isolated incident rather than a pattern of criminal behavior. Furthermore, the defendant has already made partial restitution, showing a willingness to take responsibility and make the victim whole. Balancing the need for deterrence and punishment for the breach of trust against the defendant's clean history and efforts to repay the stolen funds, a short period of incarceration is warranted, followed by a probationary period to ensure full restitution is completed.",
  "verdict": 6
}
